that circumbinary planets are more\nlikely to be quite common in the Saturn-mass range. Jupiter-mass circumbinary\nplanets are likely to be less common because of their less stable evolution.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 13 Mar 2008 16:15:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
